# macOS Development (Apple Silicon)

When building or running DouyinVietnamizer on macOS (M1–M4):

1. Read `docs/BUILD_MACOS.md` for tool setup.
2. Use dev workflows: `pnpm run setup`, `pnpm run dev`, or `pnpm tauri:dev`
3. Do **not** commit `backend/models/`, `backend/data/`, `.cache/`, or test WAV artifacts.
4. This platform uses Metal/CPU — not CUDA. Do not apply Windows-only CUDA build steps on macOS.
